    "narrative": "The Austin Waves\u2019 offensive outlook for May 4th hinges on a trio of high-upside plays, led by **Josh Lowe** (71.44) and **Gunnar Henderson** (70.02). **Josh Lowe** sits at the top of our lineup efficiency, benefiting from a favorable matchup against Davis Martin (4.38 xERA) and a helpful wind direction that boosts his power profile. Similarly, **Gunnar Henderson** remains a focal point for our 5x5 Roto chase; despite a daunting opponent in Schlittler, his elite leadoff position and favorable platoon dynamic command a top-tier start. **Heliot Ramos** (69.27) also enters elite territory, as the combination of an advantageous wind and a weak matchup against Randy V\u00e1squez (4.91 xERA) provides the highest SP-related upside of any player on our roster today.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the card involved **Dominic Smith** (36.41), who hovered on the periphery of our utility spot but ultimately failed to crack the starting nine. While **Dominic Smith** possesses the platoon advantage to potentially outperform lower-tier starters, the lack of official lineup confirmation coupled with his lower floor relative to **Nolan Schanuel** (64.36) forced him to the bench to preserve our game caps. Meanwhile, we continue to monitor the status of **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Jordan Westburg**, whose lingering absences on the IL force us to lean heavily on the depth provided by **Jackson Merrill** (53.85) and **Miguel Vargas** (49.47). \n\nStrategy for today remains focused on balancing individual scoring potential against the scarcity of stolen bases. We are cautiously watching the \"Lineup Pending\" designations for **Sam Antonacci**, **Miguel Vargas**, and **Jackson Merrill**; should any of these players drop lower in their respective batting orders, their dynamic scoring advantages\u2014largely driven by order-based multipliers\u2014will necessitate a re-evaluation of the daily efficiency scores. With **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (65.92) providing a solid 